Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.05,0:00:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.31,0:00:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you're having a great
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.86,0:00:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,WWDC.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.21,0:00:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Building Great
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.22,0:00:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Document-based Apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.95,0:00:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we are going to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.74,0:00:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,all the new features of the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.41,0:00:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Files app and how to integrate
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.76,0:00:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,them in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.58,0:00:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let's talk about the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.94,0:00:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Files app.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.87,0:00:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the biggest features of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.34,0:00:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,this app is that it gathers all
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.25,0:00:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the cloud vendors in one place.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.31,0:00:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This is done thanks to the new
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.81,0:00:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,file provider extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.42,0:00:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All the cloud vendors that use
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.12,0:00:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this file provider extension
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.61,0:00:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,will appear next to the iCloud
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.51,0:00:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,drive on my iPad in the sidebar.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.44,0:01:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to know more about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.22,0:01:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,this extension, we invite you to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.32,0:01:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,check out the File Provider
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.26,0:01:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Enhancements session tomorrow at
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.77,0:01:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,11:00 a.m. There are two file
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.16,0:01:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,providers by default in the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.43,0:01:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,system.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.27,0:01:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one is the iCloud
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.11,0:01:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Drive provider.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.81,0:01:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It will show all the files
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.00,0:01:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,inside the iCloud drive folder
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.26,0:01:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of the user as well as all the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.18,0:01:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,files in the Cloud container of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.77,0:01:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,all the applications in the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.08,0:01:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,system.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.02,0:01:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The second provider is the on my
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.37,0:01:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,iPad provider.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.73,0:01:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It will let the user leverage
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.39,0:01:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the storage of their devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.66,0:01:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It will show the content inside
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.20,0:01:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the Documents folder of the app
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.87,0:01:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,container.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.41,0:01:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want your app to be part
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.61,0:01:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of this local storage provider,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.20,0:01:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,your app needs to be a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.05,0:01:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,document-based app or support
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.77,0:01:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,File Sharing and Opening
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.60,0:01:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Documents In Place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.12,0:01:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said before, we are going
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.76,0:01:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to be showing the documents
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.11,0:01:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,inside the, the files inside the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.53,0:01:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Documents folder.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.67,0:01:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So please keep the content of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.72,0:01:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,this folder clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.15,0:01:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You should only have the files
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.68,0:01:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that matter to the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.54,0:02:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, you have to keep in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.28,0:02:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that these files won't be synced
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.55,0:02:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,across multiple devices but
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.28,0:02:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,still will be part of the iCloud
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.25,0:02:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,backup.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.41,0:02:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I would like to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.27,0:02:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the new Recents view.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.29,0:02:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This view will show all the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.47,0:02:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,documents that have been
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.61,0:02:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,recently opened, imported, and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.43,0:02:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,modified.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.69,0:02:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, it will show all the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.17,0:02:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,documents organized by tags and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.76,0:02:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,all the documents that are
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.79,0:02:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,shared with other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.08,0:02:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Tags are a great means to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.47,0:02:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,organize files.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.05,0:02:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And in iOS 11, there's new
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.24,0:02:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,tagging UI that will let the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.74,0:02:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,user create new tag and manage
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.96,0:02:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,their tags.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.44,0:02:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Tags will be synced across
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.67,0:02:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple providers and they will
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.09,0:02:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,be also synced across all your
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.58,0:02:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.58,0:02:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing -- The last
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.95,0:02:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,feature I would like to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.73,0:02:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about in the Files App is the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.32,0:02:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Recents Popover.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.84,0:02:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The user will be able to present
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.53,0:02:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,this popover when performing a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.23,0:02:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,long press on the Files App.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.69,0:02:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This [inaudible] will show all
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.21,0:03:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the recent documents and the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.66,0:03:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,user will be able to open them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.28,0:03:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with just one tap.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.95,0:03:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It will also let the user import
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.20,0:03:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the document into any
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.40,0:03:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,application using the new Drag
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.34,0:03:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and Drop gesture.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.42,0:03:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure now you want to have
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.18,0:03:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,all these great features in your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.25,0:03:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.18,0:03:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout the last release
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.04,0:03:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,cycles, we've received very many
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.55,0:03:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,requests from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.38,0:03:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to have a unified UI
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.44,0:03:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for file browsing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.43,0:03:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You want your app to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.75,0:03:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,access any file from other apps
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.96,0:03:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.18,0:03:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't want to write more
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.24,0:03:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,code in order to adopt all the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.27,0:03:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,cloud vendors that are already
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.59,0:03:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,part of the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.66,0:03:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And you want to have deeper
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.82,0:03:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,integration of your custom
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.10,0:03:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,content types throughout system.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.99,0:03:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well today we are going to view
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.02,0:03:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,some new API.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.95,0:03:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I will tell later how we've done
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.73,0:03:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so far with those requests.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.17,0:03:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I would like to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.94,0:04:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,about the new document browser
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.70,0:04:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,API.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.30,0:04:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This year there's a new class,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.69,0:04:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the UI Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.05,0:04:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.57,0:04:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's a mouthful, so from
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.40,0:04:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,now on I will call it the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.40,0:04:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser VC.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.56,0:04:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Together with this, there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.80,0:04:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,new Xcode template that will let
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.77,0:04:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you create a new document-based
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.78,0:04:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,application from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.15,0:04:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And also the UI Document Picker
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.49,0:04:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,will get some of the features of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.93,0:04:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the Browser VC.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.76,0:04:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So now let's first talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.36,0:04:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the Browser View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.36,0:04:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This view controller will
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.26,0:04:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,provide your app the same
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.61,0:04:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,feature set as Files app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.79,0:04:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Files is just a very
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.32,0:04:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,thin layer on top of this
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.62,0:04:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.43,0:04:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,With this view controller, you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.01,0:04:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,won't have to write more code in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.10,0:04:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,order to integrate any cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.59,0:04:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,storage provider that supports
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.27,0:04:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,File Provider.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.98,0:04:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Also it will support appearance
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.47,0:04:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,customization to make it look
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.24,0:04:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,like your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.29,0:05:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And by using this view
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.04,0:05:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,controller, your app will get
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.99,0:05:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the Recents Popover that we saw
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.82,0:05:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.85,0:05:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Spotlight plays a key role in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.97,0:05:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,this Browser VC.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.54,0:05:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,By using this view controller,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.56,0:05:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,all the metadata of your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.54,0:05:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,document will automatically be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.88,0:05:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,indexed in Spotlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.67,0:05:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need to have further
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.44,0:05:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,integration, you will have to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.83,0:05:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,register your own CS Searchable
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.71,0:05:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Items.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.12,0:05:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there will be two CS
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.43,0:05:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Searchable Item in the system as
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.59,0:05:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to duplicate them, the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.27,0:05:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser VC will use a content
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.36,0:05:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,URL of this CS Searchable Items.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.68,0:05:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to set it properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.26,0:05:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to know more about
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.57,0:05:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Core Spotlight, there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.93,0:05:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,session at 4:10 p.m. today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.74,0:05:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,At Apple, we deeply care about
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.16,0:05:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,our user's privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.62,0:05:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of that, we built the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.52,0:05:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser View Controller with
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.29,0:05:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,privacy in mind since the very
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.11,0:05:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.81,0:05:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When the user installs your app,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.86,0:05:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you will only have access to all
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.15,0:05:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the documents inside the app
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.18,0:06:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,container.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.51,0:06:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be able to import and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.11,0:06:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,create new documents but only
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.88,0:06:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the default safe location which
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.82,0:06:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,will be a [inaudible] for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.44,0:06:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So how are you going to access
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.49,0:06:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to a file in any other place in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.80,0:06:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the system?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.88,0:06:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you will do it via user
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.44,0:06:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.65,0:06:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The Browser VC is running in a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.17,0:06:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,different process.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.98,0:06:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And once the user taps on a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.77,0:06:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,document, the Browser VC will
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.83,0:06:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,forward to your app the access
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.71,0:06:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of that document.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.40,0:06:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, let's take a look at
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.40,0:06:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the UI Document Picker View
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.93,0:06:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.41,0:06:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said before, we'll get some
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.55,0:06:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of the features of the Browser
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.37,0:06:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,VC.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.88,0:06:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, the Browse View and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.97,0:06:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the Recents View.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.95,0:06:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, it will support opening
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.68,0:06:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and importing multiple documents
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.17,0:06:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.53,0:06:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to support it, you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.67,0:06:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,need to set the allows Multiple
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.26,0:06:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Selection to true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.11,0:06:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to support multiple
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.17,0:06:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,documents, we are deprecating
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.13,0:06:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the document picker with Pick
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.55,0:06:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Document At URL delegate method
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.44,0:06:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in favor of a delegate method
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.77,0:06:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that support multiple URLs at
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.56,0:07:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.28,0:07:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Also this year, we are
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.29,0:07:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,deprecating the UI Document Menu
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.86,0:07:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller in favor of the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.62,0:07:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,UI Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.80,0:07:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.20,0:07:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, we've seen an overview
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.21,0:07:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of the browser APIs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.46,0:07:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at how to make
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.99,0:07:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,use of this UI Document Browser
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.99,0:07:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.77,0:07:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So first things first.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.49,0:07:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You will have to configure the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.68,0:07:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Info.plist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.86,0:07:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you need to set the UI
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.69,0:07:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Supports Document Browser key to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.81,0:07:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.94,0:07:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This will tell the system that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.74,0:07:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,your app is a UI Document Brower
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.33,0:07:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,based application.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.32,0:07:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you will need to declare
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.08,0:07:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the content types that are
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.18,0:07:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,supported by your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.85,0:07:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is important because
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.99,0:07:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the Browser VC will use this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.20,0:07:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,content type in order to know
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.69,0:07:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,what files to display in your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.05,0:07:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.18,0:07:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important to note that the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.28,0:07:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,UI Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.25,0:07:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller needs to be the root
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.18,0:07:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller of your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.91,0:07:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't work otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.76,0:07:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said before, the Browser VC
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.24,0:08:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,supports appearance
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.05,0:08:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,customization.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.25,0:08:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,By default, it will look like
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.58,0:08:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,this with a white background and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.38,0:08:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a blue tint color.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.18,0:08:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two properties that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.76,0:08:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you can use in order to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.88,0:08:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,customize it further.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.48,0:08:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The browser Interface Style
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.08,0:08:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,which has three modes, dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.11,0:08:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,white, and light, and tint
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.98,0:08:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,color.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.33,0:08:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you use a dark style and an
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.33,0:08:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,orange tint color, your app will
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.09,0:08:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,look like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.50,0:08:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that we configured the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.18,0:08:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser VC, the first thing your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.27,0:08:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,app will have to support is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.68,0:08:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Opening Documents.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.69,0:08:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look at how it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.64,0:08:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,works.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.93,0:08:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the user will tap on one
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.49,0:08:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of these documents.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.61,0:08:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, the Browser VC will fetch
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.69,0:08:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and download the information of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.14,0:08:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the document.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.68,0:08:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And once the document is ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.68,0:08:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it will forward the access to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.00,0:08:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,your application and call the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.72,0:08:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,did Pick Delegate method.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.76,0:08:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you just need to load and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.07,0:08:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,present the document.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.42,0:08:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When opening documents, the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.61,0:09:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser VC will give your app
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.18,0:09:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,persistent access to that URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.00,0:09:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you want to restore it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.78,0:09:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not enough to store the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.65,0:09:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.96,0:09:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to store the bookmark
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.26,0:09:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,data associated to this URL
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.18,0:09:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is the piece of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.65,0:09:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,information that keeps track of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.15,0:09:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the URL access.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.70,0:09:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The code to Opening Document
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.99,0:09:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,looks like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.61,0:09:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You just need to implement the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.95,0:09:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,document Browser did Pick
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.37,0:09:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Document URLs and present the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.94,0:09:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller for the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.86,0:09:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,document.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.83,0:09:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the UI Document Picker, the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.16,0:09:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser VC supports opening
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.73,0:09:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple documents at the same
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.90,0:09:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.86,0:09:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want your app to support
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.47,0:09:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this, you need to set the allows
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.96,0:09:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Picking Multiple Items to true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.62,0:09:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that your app is able to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.89,0:09:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,open any file in the system, the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.63,0:09:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,next thing is to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.87,0:09:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,create new documents.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.47,0:09:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two places where you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.82,0:09:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,can create new documents.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.62,0:09:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one is the Recents
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.69,0:09:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,View.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.57,0:09:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If the user taps the Create
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.73,0:09:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,button here, it will create a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.15,0:09:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,new document in the default safe
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.19,0:10:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,location of your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.39,0:10:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you tap the Create button in
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.68,0:10:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the Browse View, it will create
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.22,0:10:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a new document in the current
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.11,0:10:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,location of the Browse View.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.06,0:10:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.84,0:10:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,workflow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.25,0:10:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the user taps on one of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.67,0:10:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,these Create buttons, your app
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.90,0:10:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,will receive an import handler.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.35,0:10:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if you already have the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.45,0:10:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,source URL, you can call the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.00,0:10:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,import handler.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.50,0:10:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If not, if your app needs to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.48,0:10:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,show some template chooser in
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.08,0:10:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,order to know what source URL to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.14,0:10:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,choose, now is the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.38,0:10:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You present a template chooser
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.66,0:10:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and call the import handler.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.59,0:10:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The import handler will move
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.07,0:10:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that file to the provider.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.26,0:10:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And once the file is in the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.04,0:10:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,provider, it will call you back
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.88,0:10:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with a succeed delegate method.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.09,0:10:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, as for the open case, you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.31,0:10:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,just need to load and present
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.78,0:10:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the document.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.07,0:10:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the import operation can
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.94,0:10:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,fail for many reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.89,0:10:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that is the case, you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.13,0:10:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,need to handle the error and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.57,0:10:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,present some UI to the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.84,0:10:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's take a look at how to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.36,0:10:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,code this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.57,0:11:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,First you need to implement the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.05,0:11:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,document Browser did Request
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.46,0:11:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.98,0:11:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, as I said before, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.69,0:11:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,optionally present a Template
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.91,0:11:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Chooser.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.06,0:11:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in this example, the present
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.68,0:11:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Template Chooser will call us
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.40,0:11:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,back with the URL that the user
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.90,0:11:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,picked for the template.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.87,0:11:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And it will tell us if the user
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.75,0:11:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,canceled the document creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.02,0:11:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we get the URL, we just
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.27,0:11:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,need to call the import handler
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.43,0:11:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,with a mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.45,0:11:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two different modes:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.87,0:11:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,copy and move.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.44,0:11:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If the user canceled the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.78,0:11:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,document creation, we still need
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.40,0:11:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to call the import handler with
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.18,0:11:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,nil as the URL and none as the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.68,0:11:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.62,0:11:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.82,0:11:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This will tell the Browser VC
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.77,0:11:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that the creation operation is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.16,0:11:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.18,0:11:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the document is fully
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.72,0:11:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,imported, the document Browser
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.33,0:11:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,did Import Document At source
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.95,0:11:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,URL to Destination URL will be
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.88,0:11:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,called.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.70,0:11:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you just need to load and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.61,0:11:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,present the UI for the document.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.89,0:11:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said before, the import
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.58,0:11:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,operation can fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.44,0:12:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that is the case, the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.04,0:12:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Browser failed To
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.31,0:12:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Import Document URL will be
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.20,0:12:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,called.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.75,0:12:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you need to handle the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.94,0:12:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,error and present some UI to the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.30,0:12:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,user.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.19,0:12:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we are dealing with
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.98,0:12:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,documents that are operated by
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.56,0:12:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,different processes, different
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.52,0:12:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,apps, and different devices at
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.46,0:12:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.38,0:12:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And because of that, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.21,0:12:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,important to use NS File
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.52,0:12:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Coordination and NS File
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.03,0:12:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Presenter in order to avoid risk
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.98,0:12:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions between these
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.98,0:12:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,processes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.62,0:12:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now because the document is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.75,0:12:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,outside your app container, the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.85,0:12:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser VC is using
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.90,0:12:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Security-scoped URLs, which
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.79,0:12:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,means you have to start and stop
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.51,0:12:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,accessing that URL in order to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.46,0:12:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,have the right to write and read
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.70,0:12:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.13,0:12:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We highly encourage you to use
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.32,0:12:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,UI Document.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.71,0:12:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,By using it, you will get File
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.80,0:12:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Coordination, File Presenter,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.42,0:12:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and Security-scoped URL support
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.29,0:12:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for free, as well as other
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.80,0:12:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,features like Autosave.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.54,0:12:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to know more about
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.33,0:12:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,UI Document, please take a look
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.21,0:12:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,at the Building Document-Based
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.46,0:13:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Apps session from WWDC 2015.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.63,0:13:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I would like to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.60,0:13:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,introduce my colleague Raffeal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.13,0:13:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to give you a demo on how to use
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.74,0:13:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the UI Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.84,0:13:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller in your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.68,0:13:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Raffael
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.02,0:13:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.82,0:13:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.62,0:13:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Pau.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.27,0:13:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.46,0:13:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that you've got to know
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.65,0:13:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the API of the new UI Document
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.39,0:13:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser View Controller, I would
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.79,0:13:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,like to walk you through and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.77,0:13:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,show a demo of how easy it is to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.76,0:13:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,build a great document-based app
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.63,0:13:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,for iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.06,0:13:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to build a very
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.47,0:13:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,simple particle editor with a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.07,0:13:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,particle system on the left and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.10,0:13:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,an inspect on the right side
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.35,0:13:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that allows you to customize
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.49,0:13:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,some properties of the particle
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.64,0:13:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,system.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.97,0:13:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now each particle system comes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.71,0:13:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,within one document and,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.18,0:13:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore, using the UI Document
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.81,0:13:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser View Controller is a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.16,0:13:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect choice for our
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.41,0:13:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.69,0:13:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So now let's just switch to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.75,0:13:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.02,0:14:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode 11 comes with a new
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.80,0:14:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,template for document-based
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.22,0:14:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.30,0:14:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.16,0:14:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to call it particles and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.10,0:14:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,create the new application.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.24,0:14:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now once instantiated, this
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.64,0:14:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,template comes with everything
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.95,0:14:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to build a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.89,0:14:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,document-based application from
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.33,0:14:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.66,0:14:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, the Info.plist of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.36,0:14:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,our target is already set up the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,way Pau mentioned it earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.63,0:14:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,with the right key.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.22,0:14:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we have a Document Browser
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.34,0:14:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller subclass that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.07,0:14:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,has all the code already in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.49,0:14:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,place that you might want to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.76,0:14:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,customize later.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.63,0:14:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It also comes with a view
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.31,0:14:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,controller subclass, the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.72,0:14:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Document View Controller which
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.40,0:14:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,will be in charge of presenting
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.79,0:14:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the contents of our files.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.58,0:14:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, as Pau mentioned also
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.69,0:14:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,earlier, we have the subclass of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.55,0:14:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,UI Document that acts as the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.26,0:14:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,model of our documents at
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.79,0:14:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,runtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.51,0:14:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And last but not least, our
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.79,0:14:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,storyboard is set up to have the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.67,0:15:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Browser View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.31,0:15:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as the root View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.40,0:15:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,already set up and the Document
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.55,0:15:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller ready to be
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.83,0:15:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,instantiated when we create new
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.56,0:15:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,files or open existing files.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.45,0:15:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's just take a look at
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.54,0:15:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what we get just by launching
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.83,0:15:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,this template in our simulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.03,0:15:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now once started, we see the new
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.51,0:15:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Recents view with your recent
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.57,0:15:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,documents that you might have
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.86,0:15:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,created before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.98,0:15:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we haven't created
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.06,0:15:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,any files yet, so let's switch
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.62,0:15:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Browse view.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.88,0:15:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We see our Cloud storage vendors
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.90,0:15:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,on the left side in the slide
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.17,0:15:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,bar next to the new On My iPad
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.88,0:15:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,storage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.23,0:15:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We also see the Favorites and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.34,0:15:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,our Tags that are synchronized
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.98,0:15:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,across all your devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.24,0:15:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the screen, we
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.31,0:15:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,see a large Create Document
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.80,0:15:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,button that allows you to create
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.77,0:15:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,new documents.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.60,0:15:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's click it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.78,0:16:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, nothing really happens yet
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.40,0:16:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.43,0:16:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because we haven't told
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.54,0:16:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the UI Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.75,0:16:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller yet what it means to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.63,0:16:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,create new files in our
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.95,0:16:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.13,0:16:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's fix this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.36,0:16:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we switch back to our
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.05,0:16:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,UI Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.17,0:16:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller subclass.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.24,0:16:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And as Pau mentioned earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.44,0:16:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,when the user tapes the Create
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.19,0:16:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Document button, we'll get a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.78,0:16:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,call back to the Document
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.33,0:16:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser View Controller Delegate
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.78,0:16:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,function did Request Document
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.73,0:16:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation With Handler.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.82,0:16:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what we have to do here is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.01,0:16:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to give back a URL of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.37,0:16:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the newly created file to the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.94,0:16:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.84,0:16:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.85,0:16:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in our situation, let me add
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.49,0:16:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a new particles file to our
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.45,0:16:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,target.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.56,0:16:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We make sure that it's added to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.14,0:16:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,our target and finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.09,0:16:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now at runtime, we just go ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.24,0:16:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and obtain the URL of this added
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.85,0:16:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,document via our NS main bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.35,0:17:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we get the URL, we pass it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.58,0:17:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to the input handler that we get
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.04,0:17:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,from our delegate function.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.18,0:17:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And we perform a copy operation
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.15,0:17:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,on the URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.58,0:17:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the UI Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.02,0:17:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller will get this URL and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.17,0:17:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,will do all the heavy lifting
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.38,0:17:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,for you in the background like
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.40,0:17:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,moving the file to the right
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.47,0:17:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,location and processing the URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.33,0:17:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Once it's done, it will give us
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.81,0:17:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a call back to either did Import
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.27,0:17:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Document At source URL or failed
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.22,0:17:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,To Import Document At URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.67,0:17:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if we fail to import the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.20,0:17:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,newly created file, since we
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.09,0:17:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,want to be a good developer we
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.69,0:17:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,should go ahead and implement
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.22,0:17:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,proper error handling, for
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.29,0:17:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,example, by presenting an error
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.87,0:17:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.71,0:17:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if we succeeded, we can
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.39,0:17:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,go ahead and present the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.73,0:17:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,document that we've just
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.83,0:17:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,created.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.69,0:17:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's say the user has
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.49,0:17:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,picked an existing file, in that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.39,0:17:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,situation, we're going to get a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.76,0:17:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,call back to the did Pick
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.63,0:17:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Document URLs function.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.40,0:18:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Same here, we just go ahead take
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.55,0:18:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,for example the first of our
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.09,0:18:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,document URLs that we get and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.24,0:18:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,present it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.65,0:18:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now presenting a document in our
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.59,0:18:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,app means instantiating one of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.07,0:18:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,these Document View Controllers
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.52,0:18:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,giving it a document that we
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.14,0:18:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,initialize with document URL
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.73,0:18:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that we want to open and then we
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.60,0:18:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,just go ahead and present the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.90,0:18:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Document View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.27,0:18:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.28,0:18:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,simulator again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.28,0:18:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The app launches again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.02,0:18:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in the Browse view and we
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.84,0:18:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,can tap the Create Document
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.09,0:18:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.85,0:18:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Document View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.05,0:18:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,appears with details about the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.98,0:18:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,file that we've just created.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.03,0:18:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we are done, we can close
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.30,0:18:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the Document View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.36,0:18:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,again to return to the root View
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.40,0:18:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller or Document Browser
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.23,0:18:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.46,0:18:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let me switch to a more
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.42,0:18:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced version of this project
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.31,0:18:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,which has already all the code
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.70,0:18:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,pieces in place to render a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.65,0:18:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,particle system on the left and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.55,0:19:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,an editor on the right side so
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.22,0:19:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can focus on the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.17,0:19:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Browser View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.45,0:19:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,related code parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.59,0:19:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I'm going to remove the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.74,0:19:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,app that we've just created to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.65,0:19:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,avoid any further conflicts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.06,0:19:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is still the same, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.43,0:19:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,still the same project.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.31,0:19:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's based on the template that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.33,0:19:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we've instantiated in the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.99,0:19:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.05,0:19:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me show you some additions
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.21,0:19:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that we made to our Particle app
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.22,0:19:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Info.plist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.78,0:19:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,First, again, the key to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.75,0:19:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Browser View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.98,0:19:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is still set to yes, just the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.65,0:19:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,way Pau explained earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.12,0:19:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But more than that, in the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.33,0:19:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Exported UTIs section, we are
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.12,0:19:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,creating a new UTI type for our
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.34,0:19:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Particles files.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.34,0:19:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to give it a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.29,0:19:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,description particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.36,0:20:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We give it an identifier and we
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.64,0:20:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,let it conform to the UTI types
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.63,0:20:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,public data and public content.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.17,0:20:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That means our Particle files
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.18,0:20:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,are a stream of data and they
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.64,0:20:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,have a semantic of document
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.54,0:20:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,files.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.48,0:20:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in the additional exported
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.83,0:20:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,UTI properties, we defined that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.96,0:20:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,our files should have, whoops,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.08,0:20:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,sorry, should have the particles
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.43,0:20:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.09,0:20:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That means that any file in the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.72,0:20:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,system that has the .particles
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.74,0:20:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,extension will be recognized as
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.07,0:20:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a file of our newly created UTI
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.90,0:20:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,type.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.08,0:20:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that the UTI type is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.47,0:20:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,done, we can go ahead and tell
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.98,0:20:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,our application that we're
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.28,0:20:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,actually supported.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.69,0:20:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the Document Types, we
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.53,0:20:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,just mentioned our particles
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.76,0:20:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,file format again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.07,0:20:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We identified the identifier and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.61,0:20:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,any additional document type
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.97,0:20:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.33,0:20:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We define our CF Bundle Type
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.33,0:20:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Role to be editor and the LS
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.76,0:21:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Handler Rank to be owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.94,0:21:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to learn more about
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.97,0:21:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this, check the documentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.11,0:21:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So now the UTI types are
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.55,0:21:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,properly set and that means that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.95,0:21:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.02,0:21:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller will make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.34,0:21:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,users are only allowed to pick
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.06,0:21:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,documents of our new file type.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.65,0:21:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It also makes sure that when you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.89,0:21:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,search inside the Document
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.55,0:21:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser View Controller, you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.08,0:21:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,will only see search results
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.71,0:21:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that make this UI type.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.94,0:21:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And last but not least, in any
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.98,0:21:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of UI document interaction
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.68,0:21:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,control in a different
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.98,0:21:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,application for Particle files,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.23,0:21:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see the action to open
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.61,0:21:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the file in our app.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.64,0:21:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So now let's take a look at our
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.41,0:21:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,actual documents.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.53,0:21:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We switch to our UI Document
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.89,0:21:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,subclass.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.37,0:21:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now UI Document is quite
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.68,0:21:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful and we highly encourage
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.43,0:21:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you to make user of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.00,0:21:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As Pau mentioned earlier, it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.22,0:21:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,comes with a lot of great
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.22,0:21:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,benefits such as autosaving,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.14,0:21:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,file coordination and NS File
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.06,0:21:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Presenter, Versioning, and much
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.33,0:21:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,more and, therefore, the UI
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.36,0:21:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Document and the UI Document
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.77,0:22:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser View Controller are
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.92,0:22:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,literally made for each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.61,0:22:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look at what we
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.02,0:22:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,are doing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.98,0:22:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the document represents the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.15,0:22:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,document at runtime.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.66,0:22:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So obviously since we are
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.41,0:22:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about Particle systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.20,0:22:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it should have a reference to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.74,0:22:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,SCN Particle System.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.67,0:22:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the next thing we are doing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.92,0:22:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is we're implementing saving and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.28,0:22:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,loading files.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.67,0:22:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we have to overwrite
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.13,0:22:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the function's content for type
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.40,0:22:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and load from contents.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.17,0:22:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now all we really have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.71,0:22:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,here is archiving [inaudible] an
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.51,0:22:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,existing Particle system and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.71,0:22:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that works because our SCN
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.09,0:22:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Particle System already
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.38,0:22:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,conformed to NS coding.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.46,0:22:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't really have to do a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.49,0:22:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,lot here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.11,0:22:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We use a Keyed Archiver to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.59,0:22:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,archive the data or we use NS
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.30,0:22:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Keyed Unarchiver to unarchive an
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.84,0:22:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,existing one again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.41,0:22:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's all you have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.98,0:22:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,about the document.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.01,0:22:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.79,0:22:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Document View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.04,0:23:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, that's the one that is in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.26,0:23:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,charge of presenting the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.54,0:23:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,contents of a document.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.86,0:23:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So obviously, before we present
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.32,0:23:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,a Document View Controller, we
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.87,0:23:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,should [inaudible] reference to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.66,0:23:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a document.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.30,0:23:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now to set document function in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.66,0:23:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,our case is asynchronous and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.42,0:23:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that's because loading a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.14,0:23:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,document should be asynchronous
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.13,0:23:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because file [inaudible] is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.21,0:23:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.17,0:23:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We're reading from the disk and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.38,0:23:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you shouldn't do this on the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.31,0:23:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,main thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.84,0:23:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look at how we
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.84,0:23:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,should implement this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.20,0:23:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we simply keep a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.39,0:23:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,reference to our document.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.48,0:23:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We then go ahead and load our
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.78,0:23:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller and then we call
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.17,0:23:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the open function on our
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.52,0:23:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,document.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.74,0:23:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this will do all the work in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.26,0:23:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the background and will give us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.68,0:23:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a call back once it's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.47,0:23:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if anything went wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.78,0:23:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,during the loading of the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.65,0:23:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,document, we're going to get a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.20,0:23:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,call to handle error user
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.01,0:23:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction permitted on the UI
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.64,0:23:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,document subclass.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.14,0:23:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we want to be good
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.90,0:24:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,developers, we have to implement
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.09,0:24:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,this function.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.34,0:24:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If we succeeded, we can go ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.37,0:24:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and take the document and pass
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.74,0:24:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it to our particle View
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.71,0:24:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller and our editor View
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.50,0:24:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.96,0:24:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the Document View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.16,0:24:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,really is just a container view
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.61,0:24:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,controller with a particle
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.64,0:24:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,system on the left and the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.08,0:24:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,editor on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.94,0:24:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in any case, we have to call
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.77,0:24:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the completion handler to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.53,0:24:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,indicate that we're done with
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.93,0:24:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,setting the document.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.32,0:24:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's about opening a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.17,0:24:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,document.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.64,0:24:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But of course we also want to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.06,0:24:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,dismiss our Document View
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.39,0:24:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller at some point.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.89,0:24:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.40,0:24:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of calling the open
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.04,0:24:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,function, this time we call
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.68,0:24:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,obviously the close function.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.92,0:24:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is asynchronous again
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.20,0:24:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,because we are saving the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.45,0:24:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,document if required.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.60,0:24:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the completion Handler, we
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.30,0:24:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,just dismiss the Document View
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.60,0:24:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.05,0:24:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the Document View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.49,0:24:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is pretty much done at this
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.43,0:24:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,point.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.19,0:24:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can go ahead and take a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.24,0:24:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,look again at the Document
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.95,0:24:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.81,0:24:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the one that is in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.73,0:24:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,charge of presenting our
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.82,0:24:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,document view controllers,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.30,0:24:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,either when we create a new file
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.00,0:25:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,or when we open an existing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.51,0:25:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,file.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.37,0:25:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at this again.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.19,0:25:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we create a new file, we
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.59,0:25:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,get a call back to did Request
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.00,0:25:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Creation With Handler.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.81,0:25:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We obtained the URL from our NS
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.39,0:25:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,main Bundle and passed it back
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.27,0:25:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,via the import handler and a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.71,0:25:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,copy operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.63,0:25:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll either get a call back to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.31,0:25:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,did Import Document At URL or
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.15,0:25:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,failed To Import Document at
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.57,0:25:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.32,0:25:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If we succeeded, we go ahead and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.85,0:25:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,present the document, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.26,0:25:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,just the same as when we open a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.08,0:25:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,file that already existed
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.56,0:25:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,before.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.59,0:25:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now when we want to present a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.53,0:25:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,document, we instantiate the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.88,0:25:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Document View Controller from
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.05,0:25:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the storyboard and we pass the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.32,0:25:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,document via our function that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.18,0:25:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we've just completed, set
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.57,0:25:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Document with a reference to a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.51,0:25:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,newly created document instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.07,0:25:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Once that is done, we just go
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.51,0:25:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,ahead and present the Document
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.70,0:25:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.97,0:25:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at this in the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.49,0:25:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,simulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.60,0:26:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Switch back to the Browse view
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.83,0:26:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and hit the Create Document
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.89,0:26:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.93,0:26:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A new file is created.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.52,0:26:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And there we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.25,0:26:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Our beautiful particles with an
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.26,0:26:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,inspector on the right side.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.98,0:26:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We can change the values a bit,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.00,0:26:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,change the size, change the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.71,0:26:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,color.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.12,0:26:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And once we are done with it, we
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.50,0:26:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,just close the document again by
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.00,0:26:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,pressing the Done button.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.54,0:26:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Great. So creating documents and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.52,0:26:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,opening documents works like a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.06,0:26:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.77,0:26:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is one thing that I
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.01,0:26:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,don't really like yet, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.07,0:26:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.02,0:26:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller here has this white
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.89,0:26:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance whereas the particle
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.65,0:26:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller has a really
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.85,0:26:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,dark appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.39,0:26:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's fix this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.18,0:26:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As Pau mentioned earlier, there
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.54,0:26:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,are three browser use interface
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.94,0:26:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,styles that you can choose from.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.87,0:26:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,First, dark, light, and white.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.36,0:26:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now obviously, dark seems like a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.03,0:26:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,great choice for our situation
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.98,0:26:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.32,0:27:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's switch back to the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.64,0:27:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Browser View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.89,0:27:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,subclass.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.13,0:27:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the view Did Load method of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.93,0:27:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the subclass is a great moment
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.07,0:27:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to configure the document
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.15,0:27:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,browser.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.56,0:27:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In this situation, what we can
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.54,0:27:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,do is set the browser User
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.01,0:27:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Interface Style to dark and we
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.38,0:27:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,can also modify the tint Color
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.19,0:27:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of the view of the Document
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.31,0:27:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.66,0:27:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in this situation, using a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.82,0:27:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,bright orange probably will look
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.48,0:27:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,great with our fire particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.80,0:27:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.02,0:27:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.06,0:27:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the same Document
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.53,0:27:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser View Controller but in a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.34,0:27:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,dark appearance which should
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.71,0:27:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,look much better than the one
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.28,0:27:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,before once we open the Document
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.39,0:27:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.88,0:27:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the control URI now has the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.09,0:27:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,updated appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.02,0:27:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's create a new folder, call
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.52,0:27:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.52,0:28:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and open a new document.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.30,0:28:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the transition between the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.51,0:28:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,two view controllers is much
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.13,0:28:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,smoother and looks much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.60,0:28:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's pretty much all I have
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.93,0:28:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell you about the first
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.51,0:28:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.72,0:28:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And to get an overview of what
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.67,0:28:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we learned so far, I would like
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.21,0:28:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to hand it back to Pau
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.52,0:28:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.86,0:28:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So let's take a look at what
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.66,0:28:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we've seen in the demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.96,0:28:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we saw how to create a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.81,0:28:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,new document-based application
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.52,0:28:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Xcode template.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.28,0:28:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we saw how to create new
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.22,0:28:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,documents and how to open them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.66,0:28:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, we saw how to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.89,0:28:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,customize the appearance of the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.44,0:28:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser VC to make it look like
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.39,0:28:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the rest of our app.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.65,0:28:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that we have the basics
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.29,0:29:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of this Browser VC, let's take a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.65,0:29:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,look at how to get and provide a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.18,0:29:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,great experience for our users.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.96,0:29:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In this section, I would like to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.32,0:29:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about three different
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.91,0:29:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,topics: open-in-place, how to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.09,0:29:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,provide custom actions in the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.17,0:29:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser VC, and how to create a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.11,0:29:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,great opening experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.71,0:29:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So first, let's talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.61,0:29:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,open-in-place.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.02,0:29:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Open-in-place is a great feature
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.85,0:29:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that came with iOS 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.83,0:29:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It allows apps to share files
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.52,0:29:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,between them without the need of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.85,0:29:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,copying them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.31,0:29:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Also because of this, you have
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.83,0:29:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to be careful when accessing
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.86,0:29:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,those documents because other
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.77,0:29:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,apps might be already accessing
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.98,0:29:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.69,0:29:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the Browser VC makes use of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.41,0:29:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,this feature in order to open
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.61,0:29:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the files from the Recents
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.53,0:29:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Popover, so if you're using the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.51,0:29:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser VC in your app, you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.80,0:29:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,really need to make use of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.24,0:29:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,open-in-place.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.98,0:29:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're starting from the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.37,0:29:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Xcode template, it's real easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.95,0:29:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.35,0:29:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If not, you will have to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.85,0:29:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,implement support open-in-place.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.09,0:30:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.13,0:30:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,code.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.31,0:30:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we have to implement the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.41,0:30:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,application open input URL
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.09,0:30:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,delegate method.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.73,0:30:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, first thing is to check if
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.56,0:30:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the input URL is a file URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.25,0:30:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And if so, we can call the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.23,0:30:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Reveal Document method from the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.03,0:30:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser VC.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.48,0:30:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This method will reveal the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.71,0:30:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,document in the Recents View and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.07,0:30:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,call us back when it's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.05,0:30:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we can load and present the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.41,0:30:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,document as we did for open and
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.18,0:30:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.18,0:30:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If it fails, we need to handle
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.44,0:30:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the error and present some UI to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.34,0:30:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.01,0:30:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's take a look at how to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.27,0:30:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,add custom actions into this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.77,0:30:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser VC.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.60,0:30:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There are three different ways
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.76,0:30:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of add custom actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.12,0:30:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one is the UI Document
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.69,0:30:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser Action.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.93,0:30:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You can add these actions when
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.34,0:30:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the user performs long press on
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.87,0:30:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a document and when the user
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.66,0:30:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,enters selection mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.30,0:30:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to create them, you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.40,0:30:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,need to give an identifier
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.65,0:30:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,localized Title and availability
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.65,0:30:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in the handler.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.58,0:30:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The availability has two values:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.42,0:30:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,menu and navigation bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.08,0:31:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Menu will make the action appear
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.25,0:31:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,when the user performs a long
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.43,0:31:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,press and the navigation bar
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.00,0:31:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,will make the action appear when
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.76,0:31:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the user enters selection mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.34,0:31:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The handler will give you the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.88,0:31:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,array of URLs that the user
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.98,0:31:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,wants to use for the action.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.35,0:31:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now unlike the Open URL, this
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.69,0:31:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,method you will only have access
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.21,0:31:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to these URLs until your
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.65,0:31:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,application gets killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.65,0:31:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we have our action, you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.22,0:31:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,need to set the supported
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.28,0:31:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,content types.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.12,0:31:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The Browser VC will use the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.54,0:31:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,content types to know when to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.30,0:31:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,display your action.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.93,0:31:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you need to set the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.21,0:31:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,supports multiple items to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.21,0:31:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,specify if you can support
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.73,0:31:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple items at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.54,0:31:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And you just need to set the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.92,0:31:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,custom actions that you created
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.30,0:31:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,into the custom action array of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.93,0:31:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the Browser VC.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.20,0:31:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The second type of actions are
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.14,0:31:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the UI Bar Button Items.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.35,0:31:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You can add these actions in the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.80,0:31:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation bar of the Recents VC
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.33,0:31:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and the browse, sorry, the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.11,0:31:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Recents View and the Browser
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.21,0:31:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,View and you can add them in the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.73,0:31:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,trailing or leading sides of the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.45,0:31:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.82,0:32:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The third type of actions are
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.80,0:32:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the ones that you can add in the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.54,0:32:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,UI Activity View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.01,0:32:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The Browser VC will show this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.89,0:32:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller when the user
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.72,0:32:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,performs the share action.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.38,0:32:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The Browser VC will let you have
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.23,0:32:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,control of this activity view
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.67,0:32:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,controller before it gets
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.83,0:32:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,presented.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.53,0:32:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, it will let you add
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.19,0:32:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,custom actions when it's
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.45,0:32:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,creating this UI Activity View
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.10,0:32:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.56,0:32:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.05,0:32:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,code.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.44,0:32:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to add additional
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.80,0:32:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,actions, you need to implement
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.50,0:32:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the document Brower application
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.92,0:32:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,activities for document URL
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.30,0:32:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,delegate method.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.41,0:32:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to have access to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.99,0:32:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,this Activity View Controller,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.86,0:32:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to implement the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.51,0:32:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Browser will Present
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.64,0:32:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,activity View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.47,0:32:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's all for the actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.92,0:32:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now as you've seen already in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.00,0:32:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Files, there's a great opening
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.98,0:32:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,transition that goes from the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.39,0:32:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail to the full screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.13,0:32:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And Files app is able to do this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.78,0:33:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks to the new UI Document
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.28,0:33:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser Transition Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.21,0:33:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This class will let you set
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.51,0:33:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,display loading progress on top
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.81,0:33:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of the thumbnail while you are
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.54,0:33:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,loading the document.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.35,0:33:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And it will also let you animate
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.04,0:33:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,with Zoom transition when you're
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.77,0:33:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,presenting the Document View
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.75,0:33:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller for the document.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.49,0:33:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, let's take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.99,0:33:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,workflow.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.25,0:33:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,First, you will have to get the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.11,0:33:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,URL that the user just picked.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.49,0:33:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you will start loading the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.99,0:33:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,content of the document.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.91,0:33:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And while loading it, you will
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.98,0:33:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,have to update the Transition
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.22,0:33:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.32,0:33:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the document is fully
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.53,0:33:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,loaded, you just need to present
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.33,0:33:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the document and use the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.86,0:33:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Transition Controller to drive
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.64,0:33:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the animation for the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.02,0:33:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.79,0:33:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, let's take a look at how
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.35,0:33:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.61,0:33:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,First, once you have the URL
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.92,0:33:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that the user picked, you need
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.60,0:33:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to create the progress object
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.74,0:33:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that will track the loading of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.61,0:33:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the document.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.05,0:34:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you create also the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.47,0:34:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,transition Controller that will
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.74,0:34:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,track the loading and that will
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.31,0:34:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,drive the animation from the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.81,0:34:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail to the full screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.41,0:34:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you just need to set the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.70,0:34:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,progress onto the transition
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.97,0:34:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.20,0:34:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, we are ready to load the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.82,0:34:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,document.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.74,0:34:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In our example, the load
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.71,0:34:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Document method will load the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.16,0:34:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,document while updating the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.83,0:34:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,progress that we created before.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.04,0:34:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the document is fully
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.35,0:34:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,loaded, it will call us back.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.27,0:34:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, we just need to present
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.50,0:34:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the Document View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.39,0:34:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if we stop here, we will
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.96,0:34:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,get the [inaudible] from UIKit
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.41,0:34:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a slide from the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.67,0:34:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but we want to have this nice
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.79,0:34:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,zoom transition.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.10,0:34:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that, we need to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.24,0:34:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,implement the transitioning
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.48,0:34:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,delegate of the presented View
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.74,0:34:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.27,0:34:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The transitioning delegate needs
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.91,0:34:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to implement the UI View
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.03,0:34:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller Transitioning
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.17,0:34:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Delegate protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.09,0:34:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In this protocol, you need to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.11,0:34:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,implement two main methods: the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.88,0:34:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,animation controller for
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.87,0:34:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,presented view controller and
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.91,0:34:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the animation controller for the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.81,0:34:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,dismissed view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.71,0:34:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you just need to return
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.91,0:34:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the transition controller that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.30,0:34:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we created before.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.55,0:35:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I will like to hand back
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.24,0:35:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to Raffael to show you how to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.41,0:35:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,implement all these advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.45,0:35:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,features.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.26,0:35:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Raffael
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.02,0:35:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.53,0:35:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.05,0:35:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Pau.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.76,0:35:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So in this second demo, I'd like
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.21,0:35:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to show you three cool things.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.11,0:35:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we're going to take a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.85,0:35:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,look at open-in-place and how
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.74,0:35:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,easy it is to adopt it with your
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.24,0:35:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Browser View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.52,0:35:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.88,0:35:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we're going to take a look
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.04,0:35:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,at custom actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.72,0:35:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to add a new action
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.87,0:35:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that shows up in the long press
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.29,0:35:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,menu when you tap and hold a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.02,0:35:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,document.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.07,0:35:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And last but not least, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.37,0:35:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,going to implement a custom view
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.76,0:35:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,controller transition to improve
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.55,0:35:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the user experience when we open
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.36,0:35:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,an existing file or create a new
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.13,0:35:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,one.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.87,0:35:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's just jump back right
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.08,0:35:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,into our project.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.75,0:35:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.60,0:35:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,open-in-place.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.94,0:35:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Open-in-place is a great feature
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.56,0:35:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that has been introduced with
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.30,0:35:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 9 and it allows you to work
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.10,0:35:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,on the file that the user has
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.43,0:36:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,chosen instead of on a copy of
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.11,0:36:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.38,0:36:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now adopting it is super easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.63,0:36:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And, in fact, if you come from
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.12,0:36:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the document based apps
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.32,0:36:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,template, you have literally
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.86,0:36:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.63,0:36:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The way it works is when the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.88,0:36:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,user taps the document outside
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.64,0:36:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of your app, iOS will make a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.56,0:36:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,call to your app delegate to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.47,0:36:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,open the URL with options.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.47,0:36:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.70,0:36:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in this function, what we do
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.07,0:36:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is first we make sure that the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.01,0:36:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,URL that we get from iOS
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.40,0:36:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,actually is a file URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.56,0:36:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's not, we should probably
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.29,0:36:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,return because we are not in the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.49,0:36:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,situation that we expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.75,0:36:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we pass that test, we get
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.08,0:36:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,our document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.20,0:36:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller which is the root
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.77,0:36:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller of our
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.62,0:36:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.93,0:36:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And we take the URL and pass it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.01,0:36:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to the reveal Document function.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.11,0:36:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.90,0:36:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller again will do all the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.48,0:36:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,heavy lifting for you in the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.60,0:36:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,background.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.76,0:36:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It will process the URL, move it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.04,0:37:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,if required, and once it's done,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.65,0:37:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to get a call back
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.98,0:37:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,with our completion handler.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.30,0:37:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now again, if we get an error,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.71,0:37:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,since we want to be good
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.63,0:37:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,developers, we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.15,0:37:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,handle the error appropriately
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.68,0:37:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,for example by showing an alert
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.36,0:37:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,view to the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.66,0:37:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If everything went right, we
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.37,0:37:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,just go ahead and present the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.71,0:37:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,document with that new reveal
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.98,0:37:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Document URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.01,0:37:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's literally all you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.42,0:37:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,do to support open-in-place in
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.44,0:37:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,your document-based application.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.91,0:37:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's take a look at custom
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.45,0:37:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.23,0:37:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So our particle systems are
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.80,0:37:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,really beautiful, right, and we
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.15,0:37:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,might want to share them with
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.33,0:37:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,our friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.92,0:37:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to add a new action
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.48,0:37:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that shows up when you long
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.50,0:37:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,press a document to export this
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.61,0:37:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,particle system as a GIF file or
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.27,0:37:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a GIF file.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.01,0:37:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's take a look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.02,0:37:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Browser View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.12,0:37:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,again.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.00,0:37:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The view did load method is a
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.88,0:37:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,great moment to configure these
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.43,0:37:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.98,0:38:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, I'm instantiating
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.22,0:38:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a new UI Document Browser
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.57,0:38:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Action.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.51,0:38:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I give it an identifier that is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.38,0:38:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,unique throughout the app, a
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.38,0:38:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,localized Title, and I set the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.65,0:38:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,availability to menu only.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.99,0:38:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So this will make sure that this
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.84,0:38:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,action only shows up when you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.44,0:38:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,long press a document inside
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.32,0:38:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,your Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.24,0:38:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller grid.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.56,0:38:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We also have to give it a
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.85,0:38:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,handler which is the one that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.18,0:38:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,will be executed whenever the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.77,0:38:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,user taps our action.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.70,0:38:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In this situation, we just go
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.37,0:38:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,ahead and log [inaudible]to the
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.99,0:38:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,consol.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.91,0:38:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we define the action
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.89,0:38:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,supported Content Types to be
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.82,0:38:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,com.example.particles with just
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.82,0:38:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the UTI type we defined earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.34,0:38:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So just make sure that only our
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.82,0:38:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,own files will get this action
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.27,0:38:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.30,0:38:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And last but not least, all we
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.45,0:38:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do is define the custom
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.00,0:38:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,actions of our Document Browser
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.53,0:38:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller to be array
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.40,0:39:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,containing this newly created
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.73,0:39:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,action.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.36,0:39:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try it out in the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.32,0:39:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,simulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.87,0:39:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now on our existing file, we
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.97,0:39:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,perform a long press and we see
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.11,0:39:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's a new action
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.00,0:39:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,showing up here, export as GIF.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.87,0:39:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Once tapped, we see that in the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.46,0:39:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,console the handler of the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.27,0:39:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,action has been executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.78,0:39:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That was pretty easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.16,0:39:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's move to the third and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.75,0:39:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the coolest things, the coolest
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.57,0:39:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,thing that I wanted to show you,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.67,0:39:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which is custom view controller
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.04,0:39:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,transitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.94,0:39:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now when we present our
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.25,0:39:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Document View Controller, we get
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.86,0:39:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a simple slide up amination that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.93,0:39:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is provided by UIKit and that's
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.40,0:39:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,already pretty cool but it's not
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.17,0:39:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,really the way it should look
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.14,0:39:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,like.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.94,0:39:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, the way it really
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.43,0:39:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,should look like is the user
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.14,0:39:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,taps the document thumbnail and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.16,0:39:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the thumbnail grows into the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.48,0:39:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,particle system on the left side
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.38,0:39:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of our Document View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.58,0:39:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look at how we
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.55,0:39:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,can make this work.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.20,0:40:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we switch back to the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.75,0:40:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,present document function that
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.12,0:40:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we created earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.94,0:40:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the way custom View
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.02,0:40:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller transitions work is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.09,0:40:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you register yourself as the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.43,0:40:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,transitioning delegate of the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.93,0:40:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller that is about to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.20,0:40:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,be presented.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.04,0:40:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Before it is presented, UIKit
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.90,0:40:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,will call us and ask for the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.51,0:40:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,transitioning controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.65,0:40:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We give back the transitioning
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.85,0:40:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,controller and that object will
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.65,0:40:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,be in charge of driving the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.94,0:40:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,animation from view controller A
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.40,0:40:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to view controller B.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.98,0:40:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,View controller A in our
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.32,0:40:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,situation is the Document
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.52,0:40:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.07,0:40:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,View controller B is the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.22,0:40:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Document View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.61,0:40:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Pau mentioned that earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.79,0:40:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.20,0:40:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller already gives us this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.87,0:40:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,transitioning controller for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.03,0:40:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We just have to keep a reference
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.04,0:40:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and pass it back to the function
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.45,0:40:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that UIKit will call.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.31,0:40:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So first, we register ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.58,0:41:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,as the transitioning delegate of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.12,0:41:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the document View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.19,0:41:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that is about to be presented.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.94,0:41:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we obtain a new
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.16,0:41:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,transitioning Controller by
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.68,0:41:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,calling the transition
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.14,0:41:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller for Document URL on
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.43,0:41:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,our UI Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.73,0:41:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.29,0:41:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this object doesn't really
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.01,0:41:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,need a lot of configuration.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.05,0:41:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing it really needs
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.39,0:41:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is the target View.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.20,0:41:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The target View is the one that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.38,0:41:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to animate to.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.79,0:41:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And in our situation, that's the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.33,0:41:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,particle system on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.59,0:41:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We keep a reference to the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.26,0:41:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,transitioning controller that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.44,0:41:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we've just obtained via our
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.34,0:41:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,variable.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.45,0:41:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the last thing we really
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.25,0:41:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do is implementing the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.76,0:41:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,UI View Controller Transitioning
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.28,0:41:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Delegate protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.44,0:41:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, therefore, we implement the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.82,0:41:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,two functions: animation
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.19,0:41:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller for Presented View
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.57,0:41:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller and also, because we
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.80,0:42:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,want to support closing
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.69,0:42:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,documents, animation Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.36,0:42:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for dismissed view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.74,0:42:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In both functions, all we have
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.08,0:42:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to do is return the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.97,0:42:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,transitioning controller that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.16,0:42:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we've just obtained.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.02,0:42:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try it out in the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.70,0:42:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,simulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.15,0:42:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.11,0:42:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We get a nice transition from
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.61,0:42:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the thumbnail to our particle
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.13,0:42:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,system.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.17,0:42:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we're done with the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.57,0:42:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,file modifications, we tap the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.40,0:42:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Done button to close the file
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.22,0:42:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,again and we transition
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.37,0:42:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,beautifully back to our UI
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.75,0:42:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.60,0:42:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.62,0:42:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's pretty much it for the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.16,0:42:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,second demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.17,0:42:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at what we've
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.25,0:42:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,learned so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.62,0:42:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we've taken a look at how
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.73,0:42:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,easy it is to support
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.96,0:42:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,open-in-place in your
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.13,0:42:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.17,0:42:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The UI Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.33,0:42:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller really does all the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.71,0:42:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,heavy lifting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.52,0:43:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we've implemented a custom
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.52,0:43:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,action that shows up only when
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.44,0:43:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you long press a document in the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.03,0:43:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Browser View
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.92,0:43:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.99,0:43:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And last but not least, we've
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.57,0:43:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,improved the user experience a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.02,0:43:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,lot when opening and closing
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.69,0:43:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,documents by implementing a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.26,0:43:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,custom view controller
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.20,0:43:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,transition using the UI Document
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.10,0:43:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser Transition Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.28,0:43:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's pretty much it for
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.09,0:43:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the second demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.30,0:43:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And to tell us what's new on the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.35,0:43:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick Look side, I would like to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.74,0:43:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,hand it over to my colleague and
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.22,0:43:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,friend Maxime.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.69,0:43:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Maxime
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.02,0:43:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.08,0:43:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.15,0:43:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, Raffael.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.30,0:43:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Good afternoon, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.96,0:43:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you have all seen the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.35,0:43:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,great thumbnails of the files
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.84,0:43:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,app and I'm sure you wish your
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.29,0:43:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,own thumbnails could show up in
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.00,0:43:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,any document browser based app.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.05,0:43:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You are now going to see how
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.49,0:43:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,this is possible thanks to the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.33,0:43:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,new thumbnail extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.53,0:43:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently, [inaudible] particles
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.30,0:43:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,app that we're building
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.44,0:44:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout this session, all we
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.34,0:44:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,can are generic icons.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.80,0:44:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We could highly improve the user
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.22,0:44:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,experience by displaying instead
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.71,0:44:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,representative thumbnails that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.39,0:44:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,indicate to the user the content
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.50,0:44:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of the files.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.49,0:44:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can you provide
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.32,0:44:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnails of files that have
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.70,0:44:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,been downloaded and are
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.83,0:44:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,available on the device?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.89,0:44:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This was already possible before
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.23,0:44:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS 11 through UI Document.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.75,0:44:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What you have to do is create a
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.54,0:44:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,subclass of UI Document and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.22,0:44:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,return the thumbnail from your
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.52,0:44:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,subclass.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.38,0:44:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This only works for files
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.06,0:44:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,created by your application and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.28,0:44:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,this has good performance
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.37,0:44:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because when iOS will ask your
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.99,0:44:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,subclass of the thumbnails, the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.58,0:44:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,file will be already loaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.69,0:44:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a quick look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.91,0:44:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,code.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.19,0:44:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What we have to do is implement
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.13,0:44:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the file Attributes To Write to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.36,0:44:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,URL for save Operation method in
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.31,0:44:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,your UI document subclass and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.14,0:44:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,return a dictionary of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.70,0:45:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnails from this function.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.29,0:45:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is nice but this again
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.60,0:45:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,works only for files created by
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.17,0:45:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.36,0:45:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can you provide
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.27,0:45:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnails for files created by
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.93,0:45:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] applications and by
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.39,0:45:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,other applications?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.99,0:45:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,For this we are providing you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.90,0:45:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with a new thumbnail extension
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.34,0:45:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,which is system wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.29,0:45:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that this extension,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.48,0:45:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,means that any thumbnails
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.15,0:45:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,generated by [inaudible]
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.33,0:45:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,extension will be displayed in
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.87,0:45:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,any document files based app
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.56,0:45:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that displays files that your
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.28,0:45:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,extension can provide thumbnails
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.45,0:45:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,for.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.55,0:45:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This extension works with all
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.75,0:45:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,cloud vendors and is part of the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.48,0:45:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick Look framework.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.67,0:45:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how this works.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.94,0:45:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,First, your document
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.86,0:45:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,browser-based app is displaying
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.10,0:45:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,-- Let's say that the document
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.42,0:45:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,browser based app is displaying
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.87,0:45:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a set of files.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.60,0:45:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we want to display
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.12,0:45:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnails for these files to
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.24,0:45:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,have a good user experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.89,0:46:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's going to Quick Look for
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.40,0:46:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnails.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.96,0:46:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick Look, we notice that for
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.05,0:46:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,some of these files, [inaudible]
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.33,0:46:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,extension is the one that can
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.07,0:46:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,provide thumbnails, so it's
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.98,0:46:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,going to forward the request to
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.08,0:46:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,your extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.31,0:46:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Your extension will generate
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.78,0:46:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnails, return them back to
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.68,0:46:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick Look which will finally
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.82,0:46:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,forward them back to the app
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.48,0:46:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that asked for the thumbnails,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.61,0:46:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which will be able to display
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.34,0:46:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.65,0:46:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how you can get
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.46,0:46:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,started.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.47,0:46:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This is actually pretty simple
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.00,0:46:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because we added a new template
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.78,0:46:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in Xcode that contains some
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.50,0:46:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,sample code for you as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.89,0:46:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,an Info.plist.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.09,0:46:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,After creating your extension,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.36,0:46:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you will want to head to the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.19,0:46:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Info.plist file and edit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.59,0:46:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So first thing you will have to
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.48,0:46:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,do is add all the UTIs you can
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.54,0:46:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] to QL Supported
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.47,0:46:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Content Types array.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.80,0:46:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Please note that you can only
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.79,0:46:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,provide thumbnails for UTIs you
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.02,0:46:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,own and export and that iOS will
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.86,0:46:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,check for UTI equality and not
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.47,0:46:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,UTI conformance.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.40,0:47:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll have to make sure to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.02,0:47:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,list all the UTIs inside
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.92,0:47:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] of the plist.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.32,0:47:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now how can you actually provide
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.75,0:47:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnails for files?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.06,0:47:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.58,0:47:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You can either draw the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.46,0:47:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail or return the image
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.49,0:47:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,file URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.49,0:47:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the most preferred one is of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.92,0:47:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,course the first one, drawing
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.38,0:47:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the thumbnail, because it's the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.54,0:47:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,most flexible one.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.93,0:47:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.02,0:47:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So any method you will have to
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.27,0:47:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,implement in this extension will
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.29,0:47:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,receive a parameter of class QL
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.33,0:47:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,File Thumbnail Request which
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.17,0:47:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,contains three [inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.97,0:47:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The file URL, the URL of the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.35,0:47:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,file we want to send a file, the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.30,0:47:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,maximum size of the thumbnail
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.18,0:47:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which is requested, as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.82,0:47:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.04,0:47:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we have to return is a
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.46,0:47:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,QL Thumbnail Reply object
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.11,0:47:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,containing the Drawing Block and
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.57,0:47:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,context Size.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.21,0:47:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see why you need to return
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.15,0:47:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the context Size.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.60,0:47:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The maximum size parameter of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.86,0:48:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the request indicates to you the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.18,0:48:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,maximum size of the CG Context
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.19,0:48:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you can draw your thumbnail
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.50,0:48:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,into.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.32,0:48:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's say that we want to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.90,0:48:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,draw this image into our
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.11,0:48:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,context.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.58,0:48:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see at full scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.02,0:48:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it's bigger than the maximum
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.67,0:48:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,size of the Context.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.64,0:48:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we'll have to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.46,0:48:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,downscale it to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.05,0:48:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it can fit within the CG
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.79,0:48:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Context.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.21,0:48:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we load this image into
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.15,0:48:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the context we have on the left,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.98,0:48:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll end up returning a
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.91,0:48:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail with unused
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.53,0:48:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible], meaning a floating
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.35,0:48:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail, which is not what we
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.66,0:48:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,want.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.79,0:48:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll have to determine the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.32,0:48:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,correct context size in which we
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.71,0:48:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,want to draw and pass it to the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.14,0:48:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,QL Thumbnail Reply.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.07,0:48:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, our Drawing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.14,0:48:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Block will receive CG Context
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.83,0:48:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,correctly set with the requested
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.62,0:48:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,size, the context Size, and
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.24,0:48:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll be able to draw the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.48,0:48:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail [inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.08,0:48:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if you don't want to draw a
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.50,0:49:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail and you prefer
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.44,0:49:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,returning an image file URL
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.01,0:49:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,instead, this is quite simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.31,0:49:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You will receive the same QL
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.98,0:49:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,File Thumbnail Request and all
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.39,0:49:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to return is a QL
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.89,0:49:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thumbnail Reply containing an
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.00,0:49:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,image file URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.35,0:49:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, Quick Look will be
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.63,0:49:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the one that will take care of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.61,0:49:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,downscaling or upscaling of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.99,0:49:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.90,0:49:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It will keep the aspect ratio of
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.18,0:49:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,your file so that the thumbnail
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.57,0:49:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,will [inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.67,0:49:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's now take a look at how
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.30,0:49:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,this works in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.08,0:49:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The only method you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.03,0:49:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,implement is called provide
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.52,0:49:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thumbnail for request handler.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.23,0:49:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing we do in this
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.19,0:49:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,example is extracting all the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.14,0:49:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,parameters of the QL File
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.49,0:49:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Thumbnail Request.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.40,0:49:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This means the file URL, the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.16,0:49:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,maximum size, and the scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.73,0:49:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of these parameters, we
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.30,0:49:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,determine the context Size in
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.11,0:49:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which we want to do our
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.06,0:49:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail, just like in the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.07,0:50:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,example we saw before.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.99,0:50:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, as we said, we need
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.47,0:50:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide a drawing Block.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.14,0:50:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we create it and this is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.24,0:50:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] that we'll have to
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.95,0:50:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,draw a thumbnail.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.24,0:50:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So drawing Block has to return a
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.46,0:50:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,success value to indicate Quick
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.45,0:50:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Look [inaudible] it was actually
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.82,0:50:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,able to provide a thumbnail.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.23,0:50:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, we create the QL
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.36,0:50:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thumbnail Reply out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.47,0:50:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,context Size and the drawing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.47,0:50:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Block and we call the completion
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.18,0:50:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,handler with our reply as well
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.51,0:50:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as [inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.37,0:50:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we [inaudible] nil because
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.39,0:50:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we always want to provide a
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.40,0:50:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail but if for some reason
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.75,0:50:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't want to always return
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.75,0:50:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a thumbnail for all the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.47,0:50:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,requests, you will have to
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.13,0:50:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,provide an [inaudible] to
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.73,0:50:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,indicate quickly that you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.29,0:50:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,want to provide a thumbnail for
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.74,0:50:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,this request.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.59,0:50:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd like to return an image
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.55,0:50:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,file URL instead of drawing a
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.80,0:50:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail file request, you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.95,0:51:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,implement the same method but
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.28,0:51:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you call the completion handler
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.01,0:51:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with a QL Thumbnail Reply
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.25,0:51:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,containing the image file URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.66,0:51:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In this simple example, we just
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.12,0:51:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,return an image from our main
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.77,0:51:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,vendor.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.39,0:51:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,After creating your extension,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.83,0:51:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you will of course want to see
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.88,0:51:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,your beautiful new thumbnails.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.93,0:51:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see them in any document
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.75,0:51:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,browser based app that displays
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.74,0:51:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,your files.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.85,0:51:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So here, what we can see on the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.80,0:51:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,screenshot are thumbnails that
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.55,0:51:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,come from the extension of
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.12,0:51:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Particles app but we are inside
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.42,0:51:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the Recents [inaudible] Files
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.06,0:51:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,app but still we see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.15,0:51:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You now know how to build great
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.84,0:51:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,document-based applications
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.29,0:51:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks to the UI Document
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.85,0:51:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Browser View Controller and the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.67,0:51:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.17,0:51:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can you improve the user
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.35,0:51:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,experience even further?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.18,0:51:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,[Inaudible] UTIs, you will
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.06,0:51:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,likely want to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.09,0:52:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,provide previews that iOS can
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.86,0:52:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,display in any application.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.33,0:52:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We are now going to see how this
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.87,0:52:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is possible thanks to the new
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.04,0:52:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick Look Preview extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.12,0:52:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,By default, Quick Look
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.12,0:52:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] set of file types.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.54,0:52:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that Quick Look by
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.59,0:52:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,default cannot preview your
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.43,0:52:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,custom file types.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.10,0:52:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have good news because
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.50,0:52:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,starting with iOS 11, you will
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.66,0:52:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to provide previews to
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.80,0:52:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick Look and extend the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.87,0:52:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,capabilities of Quick Look
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.87,0:52:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because we are opening Quick
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.11,0:52:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Look to [inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.44,0:52:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We are opening QuickLook
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.92,0:52:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] so when you preview
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.21,0:52:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,extension which is system-wide,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.80,0:52:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,this means that again any
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.93,0:52:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,application that uses Quick Look
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.21,0:52:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,will be able to display your
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.56,0:52:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,previews and you can also decide
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.07,0:52:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide previews for
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.57,0:52:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Spotlight items [inaudible] by
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.04,0:52:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.25,0:53:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,These previews will be visible
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.23,0:53:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,when peeking on Spotlight
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.16,0:53:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.22,0:53:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,On the iPhone, that's
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.49,0:53:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.55,0:53:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Your previews will be
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.08,0:53:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] in Quick Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.04,0:53:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They will benefit from the full
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.86,0:53:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick Look experience and the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.98,0:53:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,previewed as part of QL Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.03,0:53:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller just like any other
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.08,0:53:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] preview.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.57,0:53:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick Look will take care of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.63,0:53:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,displaying a loading spinner
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.62,0:53:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,while waiting for your extension
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.34,0:53:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to return the preview.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.78,0:53:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see the flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.39,0:53:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,First, Quick Look notices that
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.83,0:53:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it can't preview file by itself
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.60,0:53:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but will ask for extension for
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.75,0:53:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,preview.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.96,0:53:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Your extension will take some
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.33,0:53:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,time to generate a preview.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.79,0:53:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Quick Look displays a
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.18,0:53:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,loading spinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.45,0:53:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to take care of
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.53,0:53:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.87,0:53:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And when your extension is ready
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.39,0:53:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to display the preview, you will
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.63,0:53:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,have to call the completion
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.59,0:53:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,handler in your code to notify
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.29,0:53:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick Look that it can actually
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.71,0:53:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,display your preview.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.40,0:53:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like [inaudible] extension,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.20,0:53:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get started pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.17,0:54:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,easily because, again, we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.05,0:54:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,new template ready for you that
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.34,0:54:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,contains some sample code, a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.04,0:54:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,storybook, and an Info.plist.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.22,0:54:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,After creating your extension,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.52,0:54:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,again you will want to head to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.29,0:54:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,this Info.plist and edit it, add
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.70,0:54:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,edit it, add all the UTIs
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.94,0:54:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible], sorry, all the UTIs
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.49,0:54:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] to the QL Supported
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.79,0:54:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Content Types array.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.37,0:54:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like for the thumbnail
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.74,0:54:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,extension that you can only
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.38,0:54:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,provide previews for images you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.94,0:54:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,own and export and that again,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.94,0:54:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS will check for UTI equality
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.47,0:54:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and not UTI conformance.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.72,0:54:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wish to provide previews
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.95,0:54:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for Spotlight items indicated by
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.76,0:54:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,your application, you will have
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.19,0:54:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to set the QL Supports
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.21,0:54:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Searchable Items key to yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.38,0:54:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let's take a quick look at
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.66,0:54:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,how we can [inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.32,0:54:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to provide previews
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.35,0:54:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for file, you will have to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.52,0:54:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,implement the prepare Preview of
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.71,0:54:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,File at URL completion handle
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.81,0:54:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.42,0:54:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And all you have to do here is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.37,0:55:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,load the file and call the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.60,0:55:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,completion handler so that Quick
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.60,0:55:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Look displays your preview.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.00,0:55:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You can call the completion
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.99,0:55:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,handler asynchronously which is
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.73,0:55:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the case in this example.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.40,0:55:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wish to provide Spotlight
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.08,0:55:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,previews, you will have to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.20,0:55:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,implement the prepare Preview of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.87,0:55:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Searchable Items identifier
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.87,0:55:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,query String, completion Handler
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.49,0:55:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,method.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.55,0:55:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The query String parameter can
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.31,0:55:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,be used to highlight any part of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.24,0:55:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the preview for the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.89,0:55:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the query String that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.71,0:55:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the user [inaudible] in
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.45,0:55:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Spotlight before interacting
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.51,0:55:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] that you index with
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.67,0:55:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,your application.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.25,0:55:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like with file example, all
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.98,0:55:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to do is prepare your
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.76,0:55:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,controller and call the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.64,0:55:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,completion handler.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.08,0:55:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You can test your preview in any
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.36,0:55:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,application that uses Quick
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.76,0:55:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, for example mail or
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.97,0:55:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,messages or in Spotlight if
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.63,0:55:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] which is the case in
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.38,0:55:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,this example.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.54,0:55:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We are here peeking on the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.43,0:55:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,result index by the particles
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.81,0:55:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,app.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.71,0:56:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to finish this
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.05,0:56:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,extension tour with a few
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.19,0:56:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,performance recommendations.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.95,0:56:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When dealing with extension, you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.28,0:56:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,always have to make sure to be
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.30,0:56:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,fast and in this case it's very
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.09,0:56:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,important.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.58,0:56:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You will have to load the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.84,0:56:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail quickly especially
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.02,0:56:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,think of a case for instance of
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.45,0:56:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the user calling in the document
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.84,0:56:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,browser you want your thumbnails
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.69,0:56:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to be there as fast as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.10,0:56:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for a good user experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.03,0:56:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,For the Quick Look previews, you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.74,0:56:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,will also have to make sure to
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.65,0:56:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,load your previews fast because
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.26,0:56:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick Look is expected to be
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.80,0:56:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.85,0:56:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Also not that you shouldn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.04,0:56:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,any background job after calling
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.63,0:56:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the completion handler.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.15,0:56:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind that with extension
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.94,0:56:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,memory is very limited, so avoid
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.22,0:56:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,linking against two large
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.19,0:56:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,libraries and check for leaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.66,0:56:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's now recap quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.89,0:56:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,everything we talked about
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.00,0:56:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,today.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.78,0:57:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we talked about some
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.58,0:57:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,document browser APIs.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.61,0:57:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We mainly talked about UI
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.80,0:57:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Document Browser View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.25,0:57:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and how you can make use of it
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.49,0:57:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to create a great document-based
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.83,0:57:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.98,0:57:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You learned about its basic and
